        <h2 id="examples">Real Facebook Marketplace examples</h2>
        <p>Here are three patterns that consistently generate results on Marketplace.</p>

        <h3>1. Local furniture reseller — 3x saves through photo optimization</h3>
        <p>A DTC furniture reseller found that listings with staged, well-lit photos against a neutral background received 3x more saves and messages than the same items photographed against cluttered backgrounds. They standardized their photo setup and saw average days-to-sale drop from 14 to 5.</p>

        <h3>2. Car dealership — lower cost per lead vs third-party portals</h3>
        <p>A mid-size dealership listed 60 vehicles on Facebook Marketplace alongside their AutoTrader and Cars.com listings. Facebook generated 40% of total leads at roughly one-fifth the cost per lead. The key: Marketplace buyers were already local and used Messenger for quick negotiation.</p>

        <h3>3. Local fitness studio — 40% lower cost per lead</h3>
        <p>A local fitness studio promoted membership packages in the Marketplace services category, geo-targeting within a 5-mile radius. Cost per lead dropped 40% in 3 months compared to running Facebook feed ads targeting the same area.</p>

        <h2 id="vs-related">Facebook Marketplace vs Facebook Shops — which to use</h2>
        <p>Both are e-commerce tools inside Facebook, but they serve different purposes.</p>

        <div class="pros-cons">
          <div class="pros-card">
            <h4>Use Facebook Marketplace when</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Selling one-off or second-hand items</li>
              <li>Targeting local buyers by geography</li>
              <li>You want free, browse-intent traffic</li>
              <li>Listing vehicles or real estate</li>
              <li>Testing demand before building a full store</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="cons-card">
            <h4>Use Facebook Shops when</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>You have a curated product catalog</li>
              <li>Selling new inventory at fixed prices</li>
              <li>You want Instagram and Facebook integration</li>
              <li>Building a branded storefront experience</li>
              <li>Running product-level retargeting ads</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 id="best-practices">6 best practices for Facebook Marketplace sellers</h2>
        <ol>
          <li><strong>Use all 10 photo slots.</strong> Listings with 10 photos get significantly more clicks than listings with 1-2 photos. Show every angle, include close-ups of any wear or defects, and photograph the item in use where relevant.</li>
          <li><strong>Write keyword-rich titles.</strong> Facebook's search is keyword-based. Include brand, model, size, color, and condition in the title — e.g., "Apple MacBook Pro 14-inch M3 2024 Space Gray — Like New" rather than just "MacBook".</li>
          <li><strong>Price competitively at listing, not after inquiries.</strong> Buyers filter by price range. A listing priced 10-15% below comparable items appears in more filtered searches and sells faster on average.</li>
          <li><strong>Enable Messenger auto-replies.</strong> Response time affects Marketplace ranking. Set up an instant auto-reply confirming you received the message — this improves your "Very Responsive" badge and listing rank.</li>
          <li><strong>Relist at regular intervals.</strong> Listings lose visibility as they age. Renewing or deleting and re-posting every 7 days resets the recency signal and pushes your listing back to the top of local feeds.</li>
          <li><strong>Use the "Boost Listing" option for high-value items.</strong> For items above $500, a $5-20 Marketplace boost extends reach to buyers outside your immediate area who match buyer intent profiles.</li>
        </ol>

        <div class="callout callout-warn">
          <div class="callout-label">Common mistake — ignoring response time</div>
          <p>Facebook Marketplace ranks sellers with fast response times higher in search results and awards a "Very Responsive" badge to profiles that reply within 1 hour. Sellers who respond within 24+ hours consistently see their listings buried. Set up Messenger auto-replies and check the app twice daily during active listings.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 id="mistakes">Common Facebook Marketplace mistakes to avoid</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Vague titles</strong> — "iPhone" ranks far below "Apple iPhone 15 Pro 256GB Black Unlocked — Excellent"</li>
          <li><strong>No price or "make offer" only</strong> — buyers filter by price and skip unpriced listings</li>
          <li><strong>Hiding defects in photos</strong> — leads to cancellations, negative reviews, and account flags</li>
          <li><strong>Letting listings age without renewal</strong> — a 30-day-old listing gets minimal distribution</li>
          <li><strong>Not cross-posting to relevant Groups</strong> — many Marketplace buyers also browse buy-and-sell Groups; share listings where permitted</li>
          <li><strong>Scam avoidance failure</strong> — never accept overpayment checks, never ship before cleared payment, prefer local cash for high-value items</li>
        </ul>

        <h2 id="how-thestacc-helps">How theStacc helps with Facebook Marketplace and social selling</h2>
        <p>Managing Marketplace listings alongside organic social content, Google Business Profile, and review responses is a volume problem. theStacc's platform helps by:</p>
